# Example 2 — Add and Subtract Rational Expressions with Polynomial Denominators

Simplify

`(2x + 1) / (x^2 + 2x - 15) - 7 / (5x - 15)`

Factor the denominators:

* `x^2 + 2x - 15 = (x - 3)(x + 5)`
* `5x - 15 = 5(x - 3)`

The LCD is:

`5(x - 3)(x + 5)`

Rewrite and combine:

`(5(2x + 1) - 7(x + 5)) / (5(x - 3)(x + 5))`

`= (10x + 5 - 7x - 35) / (5(x - 3)(x + 5))`

`= (3x - 30) / (5(x - 3)(x + 5))`

