# Example 3 — Use Addition and Subtraction of Rational Expressions

The rate at which some oil wells pump oil can be modeled by:

`20/x + 200x/(3x^2 + 20)`

Simplify the expression.

Use the LCD `x(3x^2 + 20)`:

`20(3x^2 + 20) / (x(3x^2 + 20)) + 200x(x) / (x(3x^2 + 20))`

Combine:

`(60x^2 + 400 + 200x^2) / (3x^3 + 20x)`

`= (260x^2 + 400) / (3x^3 + 20x)`

